IN THE BEGINNING THE BOY THOUGHT HIS FAMILY WAS RICH, BUT HIS PARENTS INFORMED HIM THAT HE WAS MISTAKEN.
AFTER THIS CONVERSATION HIS FATHER GOT A NEW JOB AS THE JANITOR IN A LIBRARY, AND THE FAMILY LIVED IN THE LIBRARY.
THE BOY WAS EMBARRASSED FOR A GOOD PART OF HIS YOUTH ABOUT HIS FAMILY'S STATUS AS WELL AS LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
HOWEVER, HE ALWAYS HAD ACCESS TO A TREASURE TROVE OF KNOWLEDGE, AND HE TOOK ADVANTAGE OF THIS FACT.
HIS LOVE OF READING, HIS PASSION FOR EDUCATION AND KNOWING THINGS SPURRED ON HIS GROWTH AND DEVELOPMENT INTO A YOUNG MAN.
HE WAS THE FIRST PERSON IN HIS FAMILY TO GO TO COLLEGE, AND EVENTUALLY HE BECAME A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.
ONE DAY HE TOOK HIS FATHER TO HIS COLLEGE, SHOWED HIM THE CLASSROOM HE TAUGHT IN, AND HIS NAME "PROFESSOR CLARK" WAS ON THE BOARD.
HIS FATHER DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING, BUT PROFESSOR CLARK GLEANED THAT HIS FATHER WAS PROUD OF HIM.
HIS FATHER WANTED HIM TO REACH FOR SOMETHING GREATER THAN HIS FATHER HAD, BUT ALSO TO BE SOMEONE WHO LOVED LEARNING.
AFTERWARDS, HE REALIZED HIS FATHER'S HOPES AND DREAMS FOR HIMSELF, AND HE SAW THAT HE REALLY DIDN'T HAVE ANYTHING TO BE EMBARRASSED ABOUT.
THIS WAS A SHORT STORY CREATED TO INFORM THE AUDIENCE TO REACH FOR SOMETHING GREATER, AND NOT BE EMBARRASSED ABOUT THEMSELVES OR THEIR FAMILY.
FLYING AWAY ON A BOOK IS AN ADVENTURE.
PROFESSOR CLARK WAS A REAL MAN, AND HE TOOK HIS PICTURE WITH HIS DAUGHTER AT THE END OF THE VIDEO.
THE TITLE OF THE FILM WAS THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE.
HE WAS RELATIVELY OLD WHEN HE NARRATED THIS STORY, AND THIS ASSESSMENT WAS FOUND TO BE ACCURATE WHEN VIEWING THE PICTURE OF THE NARRATOR AT THE END.
HE GOT TO RUN AROUND THE LIBRARY AND HOLLER WHEN EVERYONE LEFT THE LIBRARY FOR THE DAY.
SOMETIMES HE WOULD STAY UP UNTIL 3 AM READING ANYTIME HE HAD A QUESTION THAT NEEDED AN ANSWER.
IT WAS A CARTOON DRAWING OR RENDERING.
A LITTLE BOY FOUND OUT THAT HIS FAMILY WAS NOT WEALTHY, WHICH WAS A DISAPPOINTMENT FOR HIM
HOWEVER, HIS FATHER DID GET A JOB AS THE CUSTODIAN FOR A LIBRARY, AND THE FAMILY MOVED INTO THE LIBRARY.
HE WAS EMBARRASSED ABOUT HIS CIRCUMSTANCES, AND DID NOT INVITE ANYONE OVER.
ALL HIS PEERS KNEW ABOUT HIM WAS THAT HE HAD A LOT OF BOOKS
WHILE THE LIBRARY WAS OPEN, HE HAD TO BE QUIET, BUT ONCE THE LAST GUEST LEFT HE COULD RUN AROUND AND SCREAM AND PLAY ALL HE WANTED.
HE WAS PROUD OF HIS FATHER'S WORK, ESPECIALLY THE WAXING HIS FATHER DID OF THE TOP OF THE BOOKSHELVES.
HE WOULD ALWAYS READ BOOKS, AND SOMETIMES STAY UP UNTIL 3 AM READING BOOKS WHEN HE FELT LIKE IT.
HE CONTINUED HIS EDUCATION PAST HIGH SCHOOL, INTO COLLEGE, AND WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO DO SO.
EVENTUALLY HE BECAME A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.
HE TOOK HIS DAD TO SEE WHERE HE WORKED, INCLUDING THE FACT THAT PROFESSOR CLARK WAS WRITTEN ON THE DOOR.
HIS DAD WAS VERY QUIET ABOUT EVERYTHING, BUT PROFESSOR CLARK SAW THAT HIS DAD WAS PROUD OF HIM.
HE SAW THAT HIS DAD HAD WANTED HIM TO BE SOMETHING MORE THAN HIS FAMILY HAD CURRENTLY ATTAINED, AND THE ONLY WAY TO DO THIS WAS THROUGH EDUCATION.

FLYING ON THE MAGICAL BOOK OF KNOWLEDGE HELPED PROFESSOR CLARK BECOME THAT MAN HIS FATHER FORESAW, AND HE WANTED TO ENCOURAGE OTHERS TO SEE BEYOND THEMSELVES TOO, AND NOT BE LIMITED BY PRESENT CIRCUMSTANCES.
I REMEMBER THAT PROFESSOR CLARK TOOK HIS PICTURE WITH HIS DAUGHTER AT THE END OF THE VIDEO, AND THAT THE VIDEO WAS A CARTOON RENDERING OF THE NARRATOR WHEN HE WAS YOUNGER.
I REMEMBER THAT THE INDIVIDUAL WAS AFRICAN-AMERICAN, AND LOOKING AT THE PICTURES IT WAS SOMETIME IN THE EARLY PART OF THE TWENTIETH CENTURY.
